Day 21: Yoga with Adriene - Joyful Home Practice. Its been a few days since I've done my practice. I haven't been sleeping well. I've been super unfocused and have not been able to bring myself to get a whole lot of schoolwork done. So I hit the mat again in hopes of 1, bringing myself back to my practice and 2, letting go of some physical energy so that I can bring my mind to follow and focus a little better. I didn't move as well through my practice as I may have, had I not skipped a few days. Brain was foggy through my practice but I followed along and tried to keep my attention on my breath. The breathing was good and we spent a lot of time with our hands at our hearts. That is my favorite position. It brings together breathing and stillness and mindfulness. That is something, I think, that we could all use more of in our lives. I know I certainly could. Thank you for a great practice Adriene! Namaste.

Thank you for these videos Adrienne.  I have been having a bit of depression anxiety recently which is not like me at all (I'm usually chilled and laid back) so I decided to do the 30 day challenge.  I am not new to yoga, but I've never got into the practice of doing it every day.  At first it was hard some days, but I've not missed a day, and now it is becoming part of my morning and I love it!  It is making me feel so much better.  After the practice today I did your meditation for anxiety, and at the end I cried...I have been holding a lot in and you are teaching me to acknowledge our feelings and let it go !

It honestly brightened my day so much being able to physically feel the progress my body has made by doing yoga the past 21 days! Can't wait for tomorrow!
